PN,46302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1772917927
OL,3,CWales defeated in Dublin as Ireland
OL,4,Ckeep Six Nations title hopes alive
OL,6,FWales responded through a superb solo
OL,7,Fscore from prop Rhys Carre but were
OL,8,Fultimately unable to prevent a 15th
OL,9,Fsuccessive defeat in the championship,
OL,10,Fdating back to 2023.
OL,12,FJack Conan and Jamie Osborne touched
OL,13,Fdown in the second period, either side
OL,14,Fof an effort from Wales flanker James
OL,15,FBotham, as the hosts built on a record
OL,16,Fsuccess away to England in round three
OL,17,Fin relatively scrappy fashion.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
