PN,46305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1772917927
OL,3,CWales defeated in Dublin as Ireland
OL,4,Ckeep Six Nations title hopes alive
OL,6,FIt briefly looked like being a long
OL,7,Fevening for the visitors, but Conan's
OL,8,F11th-minute finish was disallowed on
OL,9,Freview due to a knock-on by Tom
OL,10,FO'Toole before a Dan Edwards penalty
OL,11,Fcut the deficit.
OL,13,FWales grew into the game and were
OL,14,Funfortunate not to edge ahead when
OL,15,FCarre was held up over the line by
OL,16,FMcCloskey.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1772917927
OL,3,CWales defeated in Dublin as Ireland
OL,4,Ckeep Six Nations title hopes alive
OL,6,FMomentum swung back the other way and
OL,7,FWales flanker Alex Mann produced a
OL,8,Fsuperb interception to alleviate
OL,9,Fsustained pressure before Ireland
OL,10,Feventually stretched their lead
OL,11,Fcourtesy of fly-half Crowley going
OL,12,Fover in the left corner.
OL,14,FHowever, Wales trailed just 12-10 at
OL,15,Fthe end of an attritional opening
OL,16,Fperiod after loosehead Carre brushed
OL,17,Faside Robert Baloucoune and darted
OL,18,Faround 30 metres to the line to score
OL,19,Ffor the third match in a row in
OL,20,Fimpressive fashion.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1772917927
OL,3,CWales defeated in Dublin as Ireland
OL,4,Ckeep Six Nations title hopes alive
OL,6,FIreland back-rower Conan made up for
OL,7,Fhis earlier frustration by burrowing
OL,8,Fover four minutes into the second half.
OL,10,FBut Wales continued to make life
OL,11,Funcomfortable for their opponents.
OL,13,FFollowing sustained pressure ` and a
OL,14,Fbrief flashpoint involving Ireland
OL,15,Fprop Tadhg Furlong and Wales
OL,16,Freplacement Nicky Smith ` Botham
OL,17,Fpowered over in the 63rd minute, with
OL,18,FEdwards' conversion moving the away
OL,19,Fteam back to within two points.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
